28/01/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- European Affairs Minister Meglena Kuneva arrived in Washington Thursday (27 January) to participate in a seminar entitled "NATO, OSCE and the EU: Partners for Security Co-operation". 
Addressing the participants, Kuneva focused on Bulgaria's EU integration prospects, the importance of its NATO membership as well as the successful conclusion of Bulgaria's term as OSCE chairman. 
She will be meeting with representatives of the State Department and Capitol Hill, among others.
In other news Thursday, Bulgaria announced that it would be receiving 1.8m euros from the European Commission to improve the management of human resources in public administration. 
The project will be implemented in 11 months. 
(Bulgarian government Web site, Novinite - 27/01/05)
